========================================================================
ARCHITECTURE NOTES
========================================================================

1. MPAS stream manager only supports nCells/nEdges/nVertices decomposed
   dims. Remapped (lon,lat) output bypasses stream manager via direct PIO.

2. PIO decomposition type MUST match Fortran array type passed to
   pio_write_darray. PIO_REAL requires real(4). Mismatch silently garbles.

3. apply_masked packs validity mask as level numlev+1 in the same send
   buffer. ONE alltoallv + ONE SpMV for both field and mask. Normalizes
   by valid_frac, outputs SHR_FILL_VALUE where valid_frac < epsilon.

4. Fortran sequence association: passing array(pcols,nlev) to a dummy
   declared as (ncol,nlev) with ncol<pcols causes wrong memory access at
   levels k>1. ALWAYS pass explicit sections array(1:ncol,:).

5. MPAS framework calls AM init twice. register_var skips duplicates.

6. Fill value flow: AM sets 1e34 at source → remap caller detects fills
   (named constant threshold, not magic number) → zeros field + mask=0
   → apply_masked normalizes by valid_frac → output SHR_FILL_VALUE (1e20).

7. Map file uses global cell IDs (n_a = N_total), not ocean-only. The
   gcol_to_ocean_col identity branch is taken.

